The paper deals with sampling attributed networks for data mining tasks such as clustering and classification, which are common in social media analysis and other applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI) or the Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques based on Information Theoretic principles, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results over large real-world datasets, which could also place it in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
